        component end
            - One of the reasonable ends of H exclusive of the principal ends.
        principal end
            - One of H, R or HR.
        evaluation of ends
            - The evaluator is reason.
            - Any specific theory of value or other evaluative criterion is itself subject
              to reasoned evaluation: we employ it only so far as we have reason to value
              its employment based on logic, trial and error, and deliberation.
            - Evaluation proceeds in milieux where lines of thought, claims and counter-claims,
              are defeasible through public exposure.


